  "text": "-Baseline: the most commonly used hash-based approach [CITATION_1] (referred to as Hash), in which, after the hash partitioning, each data chunk is assigned to a node based on its responsible hash value. -Minimize network traffic: for each data partition, we examine all the possible destinations and choose the one that can minimize the network traffic. We refer this method as Mini. This strategy has been adopted in various advanced join approaches (e.g., track-join [4] 6 ).",
